Citations
Date: 0/0/1968
Source: Growing Better Wool
Author: HENDERSON
Vol / Page: 52
Edition:
Quote: Wool grown by sheep on copper-deficient country is often called 'steely' wool. This wool has a shiny 'steely' appearance. Steely wool can appear in sheep of any age and sex and has been described mosrtly in connection with the Merino.
